The paper discusses the application of differential privacy to Bayesian inference on probabilistic graphical models, which involves concepts from cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces novel mechanisms for private Bayesian inference, which may fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
